The paper deals with computational topology and specifically with persistent homology, which is a topic that falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the study of matchings and distances, which are topics that fall under data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) as it deals with the computation of persistent homology. Finally, the paper involves the study of algorithms and complexity, which are topics that fall under social and information networks (cs.SI).
